data.text/markdown:
Buckaroo Styling Gallery

Buckaroo can be extensively styled. This gallery shows many examples of the column configuration language. In this case all of the configs are passed in via column_config_overrides. Each call looks approximately like 
BuckarooInfiniteWidget(df, column_config_overrides={
    "float_obj_displayer": {
        "displayer_args": {
            "displayer": "obj"}}})
It is also possible to write your own styling functions that look at summary stats and return configs for columns. This is detailed in Styling Howto
